The paper deals with scheduling paradigms for distributed computations, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses mean field models to study the impact of job size distribution, which is related to Probability (cs.PF) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses bounds and optimization, which are relevant to Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA).
